  <static seed="24" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionsCalculation/EquivalentFraction10.pg">
    <statement><p>Find an equivalent fraction to <m>\frac{5}{7}</m> with denominator <m>35</m>.</p>
<p><fillin characters="8" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{25}{35}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>From <m>7</m> to <m>35</m>, we multiplied by <m>35\div7=5</m>.</p>
<p>For a fraction, when we multiply the same number in both the numerator and denominator, the fraction<rsq/>s value doesn<rsq/>t change. We have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{5}{7}=\frac{5\cdot5}{7\cdot5} = \frac{25}{35} }</m></p>
</solution>
